Pine64 says the max size of a bootable SD card is 256GB
(mine is 16GB...)



#########################
#   What the PKG Says   #
#########################

0 fran.sys ~ > cat /usr/local/share/u-boot/u-boot-pine64-lts/README
U-Boot loader and related files for the Pine64-LTS.

To install this bootloader on an sdcard just do:
dd if=/usr/local/share/u-boot/u-boot-pine64-lts/u-boot-sunxi-with-spl.bin of=/path/to/sdcarddevice bs=128k seek=1 conv=sync

For information about running FreeBSD on Allwinner boards, see
 https://wiki.freebsd.org/FreeBSD/arm/Allwinner


############################################################
#                                                          #
#   Steps GPT Says to Take to Get U-Boot SPL on There      #
#        NOTE WELL: Specific to B$'s Machine!!!!!!         #
#                                                          #
############################################################

# Install the board-specific Uâ€‘Boot
sudo pkg install -y u-boot-pine64-lts

# Sanity: confirm the image path exists
pkg info -l u-boot-pine64-lts | grep 'u-boot-sunxi-with-spl.bin'

# Make sure nothing is mounted from da0 (should be silent)
mount | grep da0 || true
sudo umount /dev/da0* 2>/dev/null || true


#################################################################
#                !!! NOTE EXTREMELY WELL !!!                    #
# The `DD` command will smoke your SD card and other disks!!!!  #
#                                                               #
#################################################################

# WRITE IT (DESTROYS the card)
sudo dd if=/usr/local/share/u-boot/u-boot-pine64-lts/u-boot-sunxi-with-spl.bin \
        of=/dev/da0 bs=128k seek=1 conv=sync
sync



